hotspot.description: The Security and Safety Management Unit (SSMU) is responsible for managing and overseeing the safety and security concerns of PNU.
hotspot.title: Security and Safety Management Unit (SSMU)

hotspot.description: The Collection and Disbursement Unit manages the cashier's office and processes payments for PNU.
hotspot.title: Collection and Disbursement Unit (CDU)

hotspot.description: The Human Resource Management and Development Office (HRMDO) is primarily tasked with ensuring an enriching, fair, and healthy working environment that promotes professional growth and career advancement for faculty members and administrative staff and guarantees a steady supply of highly competent and satisfied human resources in PNU. It develops activities that are designed to meet the needs of PNU in accomplishing its mission through the fair, efficient, and economical use of personnel in accordance with the University's requirements.
hotspot.title: Human Resource Management and Development Office (HRMDO)

hotspot.description: The Office of the Vice President for Finance and Administration (OVPFA) is primarily responsible for ensuring that PNU provides an excellent knowledge support management system. this involves the management of systems, standards, processes, practices, and procedures designed to create and sustain an environment that promotes innovation in knowledge creaton, transfer, sharing, application, and exchange.
hotspot.title: Office of the Vice President for Finance and Administration (OVPFA)

hotspot.description: The Alumni Relations Office (ARO) operations are based on a specific framework: The 4Rs – Renew, Recognize, Reciprocate, Return. It fosters lifelong partnerships between PNU and its alumni. It supports the alumni, including friends of PNU, in undertakings in and out of academic programs and concerns. It endeavors to keep the alumni fully informed about the developments in PNU, offer a wide range of services that meet the needs of the alumni, and foster links between and among alumni.
hotspot.title: Alumni Relations Office (ARO)

hotspot.description: The Financial Management Unit (FMU) is responsible for providing sound stewardship of the Campus resources and ensuring that its fiscal reputation is above suspicion. It provides financial reporting, ensures internal and external compliance, and performs financial administration. It is the Campus's focal point for ensuring compliance with laws relevant to fiscal management, and designing and implementing the Campus's fiscal management system.
hotspot.title: Financial Management Unit (FMU)

hotspot.description: The Budget Unit (BU) is responsible for the planning and management of the PNU budget.
hotspot.title: Budget Unit (BU)

hotspot.description: The Accounting Unit (AU) is responsible for evaluating and processing finance-related requests of PNU.
hotspot.title: Accounting Unit (AU)

hotspot.description: The Campus Registrar Unit (CRU) is tasked to ensure that PNU's academic policies are implemented. It is responsible for preserving the academic integrity, safeguarding the security of academic records and effectively provides accessible academic services to the faculty members, students, alumni, and the PNU Management. It serves the faculty members and students through scheduling, registration, record-keeping and reporting as well as assisting the deans and other administrative offices in providing their own services. It further supports the administration in the academic policy formulation being the principal office to provide the necessary reports and analysis required for this task.
hotspot.title: Campus Registrar Unit (CRU)

hotspot.description: The Admissions Office (AO) oversees the undergraduate, graduate, and post-baccalaureate admission to PNU. It is tasked with ensuring that the admission requirements and qualifications are properly enforced. It ensures that the University's student population is national and international in character and comes from diverse backgrounds, exhibiting readiness and aptitude for the rigors of a PNU education. It provides baseline data, conducts research, and provides policy advice in terms of student admissions.
hotspot.title: Admissions Office (AO)
Infront of the Office of the University President

userdata.title: Infront of the Office of the University President

hotspot.title: Infront of the Office of the University President

hotspot.description: The University Library (UL) exists to support faculty members and students in their academic work as the central repository of knowledge. It takes charge of book and information collection, collation, storage, inter-library networking, referral, and advocacy. UL makes these collections available to students and faculty members to meet their knowledge and information needs. It also provides venues and multimedia resources for student and faculty collaboration, meetings, and discussions for academic and research purposes.
hotspot.title: University Library (UL)

hotspot.description: The University Health Services Unit (UHSU) is responsible for management and operation of health-related services of PNU.
hotspot.title: University Health Services Unit (UHSU)

hotspot.description: The Office of Internal Audit (OIA) appraises the effectiveness of existing operating procedures and systems of internal control. The OUP works closely with OIA, which reports directly to the PNU BOR.
hotspot.title: Office of Internal Audit (OIA)

hotspot.description: The Research Institute for Teacher Quality (RITQ) contributes to achieving the University's goals and strategic directions by fulfilling its functions in research, services, and production. As a research institute, RITQ shall primarily focus on research and development in teacher and school leader quality to accommodate all efforts to improve teacher and school leader quality (e.g., capacity building, training, professional development).
hotspot.title: Research Institute for Teacher Quality (RITQ)

hotspot.description: The Management Information System Office (MISO) is responsible for managing and maintaining a competitive administrative computing environment for PNU, ensuring that the information management system is integrated, and establishing systems to make the best use of information technology to improve administration and operation efficiency and effectiveness. It provides data management, hardware management, and software management, and integration to support PNU's academic and administrative functions, as well as support knowledge management services including information retrieval, information mapping, information sharing, data categorization, and knowledge capture.
hotspot.title: Management Information System Office (MISO)

hotspot.description: The Printing and Press Unit (PPU) manages and operates the printing press and related services.
hotspot.title: Printing and Press Unit (PPU)

hotspot.description: The Research Management Office (RMO) is responsible for managing concerns related to technology transfer, intellectual property, commercialization of innovation and research projects/outputs as well as the overall development and management of research projects in PNU.
hotspot.title: Research Management Office (RMO)

hotspot.description: The Educational Policy Research and Development Office (EPRDO) is a specialized research unit in the University focused on policy research and studies on teacher education as mandated in Republic Act No. 9647 or the "Philippine Normal University Modernization Act of 2009." It is established to provide research-based policy recommendations to policy makers. It also serves as a clearing house for all data relevant to teacher education in the Philippines and beyond.
hotspot.title: Educational Policy Research and Development Office

hotspot.description: The Faculty of Languages and Literature (FLL) is a community of scholars focusing on the advancement of the field of languages and multilingual education. Faculty members focus their research on questions relevant to the teaching and learning of languages, including literature and linguistics. They provide quality instruction in developing competent teachers, teacher educators, and education leaders in the languages and literature.
hotspot.title: Faculty of Languages and Literature (FLL)

hotspot.description: The Faculty of Behavioral and Social Sciences (FB&SS) is a community of scholars in the behavioral (e.g., guidance and counseling, psychology) and social sciences engaged in exploring, shaping, and transforming people and society through the tools of research, teaching, service, and production. The faculty members focus their research and instruction integrating depth and breadth of knowledge in the discipline and pedagogy to develop learners who shall become educators and education leaders that will facilitate understanding and improvement of the human condition.
hotspot.title: Faculty of Behavioral and Social Sciences (FB&SS)

hotspot.description: The Faculty of Education and Information Sciences (FEIS) is an academic unit that focuses on the interdisciplinary and scientific practice of teaching and learning, educational philosophies and systems, and information science. FEIS advances research at the intersection of learners, education, and information. Faculty members are facilitators in the preparation and development of education practitioners who impact their communities through inclusive educational practice and relevant information studies.
hotspot.title: Faculty of Education and Information Sciences (FEIS)

hotspot.description: The Archives and Records Management Unit (ARMU) is the guardian of the PNU’s institutional memory and administrative history. It plays a pivotal role in managing both current and historical records.
hotspot.title: Archives and Records Management Unit (ARMU)

hotspot.description: The Facilities Management and Sustainability Office (FMSO) is primarily tasked to ensure a healthy and conducive learning and working environment for the University's stakeholders. It manages and records the existing facilities and equipment within the PNU system. It facilitates the provision of various services needed to maintain and prolong the life and utility of all PNU-owned properties.
hotspot.title: Facilities Management and Sustainability Office (FMSO)

userdata.description: A Geographic Information System (GIS) built by 4th-year undergraduate students from Philippine Normal University - Manila, taking up Bachelor in Technology and Livelihood Education with Specialization in Information and Communications Technology (BTLE-ICT).
userdata.title: Geographic Information System (GIS) of PNU-Manila
